</center>
</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaedreadarksoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaedreaDarksoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 12:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MANABURN - NERFED ON TEST!</span><hr size=1> Regarding how it affected small guilds.  Heres the deal.  When all these uber guilds were still doing Kunark, there was no competition by more uber guilds able to do it with less people at all times of the day for these 4 mobs.  You were the top of your server back then too.  I don't think Triton or FoH ever had to worry about uber_guild_2 coming in with 18 people when they had to gather and buff 30 and killing the mob before them just because they could.<br>
<br>
Nowadays, every uber guild can kill Talendor.  And they do, because Kunark spells are just that needed.  And they do with minimal people whenever they want.  Now what about that guild with 40 members total who has a very slim chance of finding Talendor up during prime time when they can front the numbers?  They are screwed.  They are going to have a VERY hard time getting warrior epics, bard epics, paladin epics.  If you look at the rosters of these guilds, guess which classes have the most people with no &lt;epic&gt; tag next to their name?  Clerics, warriors, bards, and paladins.  Why?  Because they can't ever get Talendor or Gorenaire or Severilious since there are 10 other guilds who can kill them easily whenever they want.<br>
<br>
What did manaburn do to that?  Yes, it allowed Wizards to form farming squads.  But as I've seen from these boards, most of the time wizards gave away the books and the scales and all to the people who needed them.  But it also allowed a guild to have a much better chance at a mob since 1 MB wizzy meant many less other people had to be there.  Up and coming guilds were getting epics at &gt;almost&lt; the same rate as uber guilds did way back when they were in the same position!<br>
<br>
With this nerf and other recent changes, the difference between the uber guild and the up-and-coming guilds is getting wider and wider.<br>
<br>
-Collectively, they have many fewer shots at Kunark dragons.<br>
-Cleric epics are 10x harder to get now.  Every old timer cleric in a high end guild has had their epic for a long time.  Hell every cleric twink made back then had their epic.  Now having 1 cleric epic is a huge accomplishment because of the Ragefire change.<br>
-Venril Sathir in its current state is many times harder than he used to be.  Rune no longer works.  I'd like to see how many non-uber guilds have even killed VS recently without Manaburn or Lifeburn around, I know my guild has yet to defeat him in 3 well-executed attempts (not zergfests), but we have offed Talendor a couple times, Wuoshi, do HoT, etc.  Strange, it was never this hard before...<br>
-Vulak is gone.  Vulak loot was a huge boon.  Now those guilds who did Vulak before the change are at a distinct advantage to those who got to NToV after Luclin.<br>
-Sontalak and Klandicar are both much harder.<br>
<br>
Manaburn helped to close the gap some, and it did very well for that.  Now, its a useless waste of 17 points and puts many guilds back into the stoneage while upper end guilds keep on moving ahead at lightspeed.<br>
<br>
I sincerely hope this change does NOT go live.  If a change is necessary to stop the farming squads, give it an icon so you couldn't have 5 wizards click at once to kill something.  You could only have 1 MB per, say, 10 seconds.  Couldn't take 4 wizards to kill him too easily then but it would still be a useful AA skill.<br>
<br>
And do NOT remove its critical element.  It takes a ton of points to be able to crit MB.  Why can a ranger with EQ and AM3 do 18k damage to a 32k mob but a wizard can't?  If anything, allow Lifeburn to critical.<br>
<br>
Well, that got kinda long, but I am quite miffed. <p><center><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78810">Sage Daedrea Darksoul</A><br>
-={60 Warlock}=-<p>
